Few key things to understand in this process: 

A. Acquirer bank charge for acquiring funds from the customer
B. Card processing fee charged by the network and the cardholder bank fee (i.e interchange fee.)
C. Usually the interchange fee is around 2% of the transaction fee.

Every time a transaction is made via #Visa or #Mastercard etc, the acquiring bank pays the cardholder's bank an interchange fee. The business then pays the #interchangefee back as part of its card processing fees.
